<h1 >Guide to Social Security Law Updates - 1995</h1>
<ul><li><a href="15300#28december1995">28 December 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#14december1995">14 December 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#30november1995">30 November 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#16november1995">16 November 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#2november1995">2 November 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#19october1995">19 October 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#5october1995">5 October 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#21september1995">21 September 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#7september1995">7 September 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#24august1995">24 August 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#10august1995">10 August 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#13july1995">13 July 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#29june1995">29 June 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#15june1995">15 June 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#18may1995">18 May 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#27april1995">27 April 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#6april1995">6 April 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#23march1995">23 March 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#9march1995">9 March 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#23february1995">23 February 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#9february1995">9 February 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#26january1995">26 January 1995</a></li>
<li><a href="15300#12january1995">12 January 1995</a></li>
</ul><h2 id="28december1995">Update 545G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 20 - MOBILITY ALLOWANCE - Remove discriminatory remark from Mobility Allowance Chapter 20. See guidelines 20.103 to 20.105.</p>
<h2>Update 544G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 17 - FAMILY PAYMENT - Changes due to the amalgamation of BFP and AFP. See guidelines 17.000 to 17.16501.</p>
<p>Re-write of whole chapter.</p>
<h2>Update 543G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 41 - PARENTING ALLOWANCE - Abolition of Dependent Spouse Allowance. See guideline 41N.7000.</p>
<p>The Dependent Spouse Allowance paid to AUSTUDY students with dependent partners and children is being abolished from 1 January 1996.</p>
<h2>Update 542G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 41 - PARENTING ALLOWANCE - Abolition of Dependent Spouse Allowance. See guidelines 41N.6200 to 41N.6206.</p>
<p>The Dependent Spouse Allowance paid to AUSTUDY students with dependent partners and children is being abolished from 1 January 1996.</p>
<h2>Update 541G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 20 - MOBILITY ALLOWANCE - Changes to the mobility allowance legislation.. See guideline 20.1010 to 20.1011.</p>
<p>Updating legislation amendments.</p>
<h2>Update 540G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - International help file. See guideline 42.2230 to 42.2233 and 42.2315.</p>
<p>Reference to the paper job aid for comparable foreign payment has been replaced with references to the international help file on the LAN.</p>
<h2>Update 539G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - International help file. See guideline 42.2510.</p>
<p>Reference to the paper job aid for comparable foreign payment has been replaced with references to the international help file on the LAN.</p>
<h2>Update 538G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Income support Supplement. See guideline 27.7100 to 27.7235.</p>
<p>Describes changes h5</p>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Portability - temporary return to Australia. See guideline 42.944.</p>
<p>Guideline 42.944 included an incorrect a cross reference.</p>
<h2>Update 536G # Date 28 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 41 -PARENTING ALLOWANCE. Abolition of Dependent Spouse Allowance. See guideline 41.3110.</p>
<p>The Dependent Spouse Allowance paid to AUSTUDY students with dependent partners and children is being abolished from 1 January 1996.</p>
<h2 id="14december1995">Update 535G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Amalgamation of basic family payment (BFP) and additional family payment (AFP). See guidelines 1.5463 to 1.5608.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 534G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Amalgamation of basic family payment (BFP) and additional family payment (AFP). See guideline 1.10700</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 533G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Amalgamation of basic family payment (BFP) and additional family payment (AFP). See guidelines 1.1403 and 1.1432.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 532G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Amalgamation of basic family payment (BFP) and additional family payment (AFP). See guidelines 1.1010 to 1.1011 (deleted).</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 531G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 23 - ADDITIONAL PAYMENTS - RENT ASSISTANCE, PHARMACEUTICAL ALLOWANCE, TELEPHONE ALLOWANCE, REMOTE AREA ALLOWANCE - Amalgamation of basic family payment (BFP) and additional family payment (AFP). See guidelines 23.000, 23.133, 23.201-23.203, 23.206, 23.1002, 23.1300, 23.1301.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 530G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Amalgamation of basic family payment (BFP) and additional family payment (AFP). See guidelines 27.24000 to 27.24100 (part L - deleted) and 27.25000 to 27.27911 (part M - rewritten).</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 529G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 9 - SOLE PARENT PENSION - Qualification and payability. See guidelines 9.310 to 9.322.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 528G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Assessment of Assets. See guidelines 27.16104 and 27.16110.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 527G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 2 - METHODS OF PAYMENT AND TAXATION - Taxation. See guideline 2.8002.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 526G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Current rates of payment. See guidelines 27.5500 to 27.5511.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 525G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 24 - BEREAVEMENT PAYMENTS - PART D - Child Deaths. See guidelines 24.6100 to 24.6380.</p>
<p>Changes due to the amalgamation of BPF and AFP.</p>
<h2>Update 524G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Clarification of "resides in or resident of Australia". See guideline 1.7202.</p>
<p>Clarifies guidelines on the interpretation of s.7(3)(f) - intention to remain permanently in Australia must not be given undue weight when assessing whether a claimant resides in Australia.</p>
<h2>Update 523G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Use of interpreters. See guidelines 1.1601 to 1.1604.</p>
<p>Minor amendments to guidelines. Linguistic Availability Performance Allowance (LAPA) now reads Community Language Allowance (CLA) and the Multilingual Telephone Information number has changed.</p>
<h2>Update 522G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 25 - NON-CASH BENEFITS - Concession cards. See guidelines 25.000 to 25.7502.</p>
<p>The entire chapter has been rewritten to reflect the current range of concession cards issued and the rules under which they are issued. Chapter 25 now contains information about the pensioner concession card (PCC), the commonwealth seniors health card (CSHC) and the 'Confirmation of Concession Card Entitlement' (Form SS55). References to the pensioner health benefits and transport concession cards have been removed as these cards are no longer produced.</p>
<h2>Update 521G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 2 - METHODS OF PAYMENT AND TAXATION - Eligibility for urgent cheque payment. See guidelines 2.3610 to 2.3613.</p>
<p>Referral of customers to social workers for financial counselling.</p>
<h2>Update 520G # Date 14 December 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Activity Test Exemptions. See guideline 45.3210.</p>
<p>Procedures for Activity Test Exemptions in special circumstances.</p>
<h2 id="30november1995">Update 519G # Date 30 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Trusts - constructive, resulting or implied trusts. See guidelines 27.15730 to 27.15736.</p>
<p>Advice on the existence of constructive trusts to be obtained from the Legal &amp; Legislation Branch rather than the Australian Government Solicitor.</p>
<h2>Update 518G # Date 30 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Maximum allowance period - role of Australian Government Health Service Medical Officer (AGHSMO) and Approved Medical Practitioner (AMP), referral to Disability Support Officer (DSO) and to a Social Worker. See guidelines 14.9500 to 14.9801.</p>
<p>Changing Commonwealth Medical Officer (CMO) to Australian Government Health Service Medical Officer (AGHSMO) and minor amendments.</p>
<h2>Update 517G # Date 30 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Education leavers waiting period - Date of Commencement: Incapacity during education leavers waiting period for JSA or NSA - Date of Commencement: Reduction of education leavers waiting period - periods of employment. See guidelines 14.7400 to 14.7704.</p>
<p>Changing education leavers deferment period to education leavers waiting period.</p>
<h2>Update 516G # Date 30 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Date of commencement - date of incapacity. See guidelines 14.6202 to 14.6205.</p>
<p>Removal of words 'deferment period' and correction of cross-references.</p>
<h2>Update 515G # Date 30 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Medical certificates and maximum allowance period. See guidelines 14.4300 to 14.4401.</p>
<p>Correction of cross-reference.</p>
<h2>Update 514G # Date 30 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Assessing use of alcohol or drugs - referral to Australian Government Health Service Medical Officer. See guideline 14.3200.</p>
<p>Amendment of Commonwealth Medical Officer to Australian Government Health Service Medical Officer.</p>
<h2>Update 513G # Date 30 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Newly arrived residents waiting periods - application to New Zealanders. See guidelines 1.10200 to 1.10203.</p>
<p>These guidelines explain why the newly arrived residents waiting period for job search allowance (JSA) and other benefits do not apply to New Zealanders and explain the exceptions.</p>
<h2 id="16november1995">Update 512G # Date 16 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 7 - WIFE PENSION - Wife pension for women under 40 years of age. See guideline 7.001.</p>
<p>A 1995-96 Budget proposal was that wife pension (WP) and mature age partner allowance (MAPA) would be abolished from 1 January 1996 for current recipients born after 1 July 1955. The Government decided on 17 October 1995 to reverse this decision. This means that all women currently receiving WP/MAPA will continue to do so, unless they lose qualification or payability otherwise.</p>
<h2>Update 511G # Date 16 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc. TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - Wife pension - partner in goal. See guidelines 1.18302 to 1.18303.</p>
<p>These guidelines redefines rate payable for partnered, partner in goal pensioners</p>
<h2>Update 510G # Date 16 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - JSA waiting period due to Agreement with NZ. See guidelines 12.5500 to 12.5502.</p>
<p>These guidelines describe the simplified waiting period rules for JSA claimants from New Zealand.</p>
<h2>Update 509G # Date 16 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Payments from insurance policies - Sickness and accident policies. See guidelines 14.4800 to 14.4805.</p>
<p>These guidelines have been simplified and rewritten.</p>
<h2>Update 508G # Date 16 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Loss of income. See guideline 14.4600 to 14.4773.</p>
<p>The loss of income guidelines have been revised.</p>
