<h2 id="2november1995">Update 505G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Rent assistance (RA) for blind pensioners. See guidelines 27.1201 to 27.1203.</p>
<p>This amendment corrects a reference to the legislative basis for income testing RA for blind pensioners.</p>
<h2>Update 504G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Assessment of saved investments. See guideline 27.12710.</p>
<p>This change corrects the reference to the Act in guideline 27.12710.</p>
<h2>Update 503G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 23 - ADDITIONAL PAYMENTS - Pharmaceutical allowance for parenting allowees. See guidelines 23.2000 to 23.2001.</p>
<p>Pharmaceutical allowance is paid to parenting allowees who are at least 60 years of age and have been receiving income support for more than 6 months.</p>
<h2>Update 502G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Saving provisions on temporary return to Australia. See guidelines 42.940 to 42.944.</p>
<p>The guideline clarifies that former residents in Agreement countries who are exempted from proportional portability because they left Australia before 1996, will not lose that exemption if they return to Australia after 1996 and do not again become Australian residents.</p>
<h2>Update 501G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 26 - EMPLOYMENT AND EDUCATION PAYMENTS - Education Entry Payment for Carer Pensioners. See guidelines 26.7000 to 26.7800.</p>
<p>Education Entry Payment is now payable to carer pensioners on the same basis as it is paid to sole parent pensioners.</p>
<h2>Update 500G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 26 - EMPLOYMENT AND EDUCATION PAYMENTS -Employment Entry Payment for Carer Pensioners. See guideline 26.000.</p>
<p>Employment Entry Payment is now payable to carer pensioners on the same basis as it is paid to sole parent pensioners.</p>
<h2>Update 499G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS. Saving provisions on temporary return to Australia. See guidelines 42.520 to 42.522.</p>
<p>The guideline clarifies that former residents in Agreement countries who are exempted from proportional portability because they left Australia before 1996, will not lose that exemption if they return to Australia after 1996 and do not again become Australian residents.</p>
<h2>Update 498G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Date of Commencement. See guideline 14.7750.</p>
<p>Payment of sickness allowance cannot commence until the expiry of a JSA/NSA/YTA deferment period.</p>
<h2>Update 497G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Payment during a job search allowance deferment period. See guidelines 14.5400 to 14.5402.</p>
<p>Sickness allowance is not payable in a JSA/NSA/YTA deferment period regardless of whether the person has claimed JSA/NSA/YTA.</p>
<h2>Update 496G # Date 2 November 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Annuities - Date Payable. See guidelines 27.13610 to 27.13614.</p>
<p>An annuity becomes payable on the date of purchase. However some types of annuity commence not on purchase date but one pay period before the first instalment is due.</p>
<h2 id="19october1995">Update 495G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Qualifications and Payability. See guidelines 15.3100 and 15.3201.</p>
<p>This amendment clarifies the ordinary waiting period for sickness allowance may be waived. ELDP may be waived for sickness allowance and job search allowance. Waiting periods and deferment periods cannot be served concurrently.</p>
<h2>Update 494G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - (1) Ordinary waiting period for sickness allowance. See guidelines 14.6800 to 14.6802. (2) Annual leave waiting period. See guidelines14.7000 to 14.7200.</p>
<p>(1) From 29 September 1995, the ordinary waiting period for sickness allowance can be waived on the grounds of financial hardship.</p>
<p>(2) These guidelines have been revised to accurately reflect the effect that the payment of annual leave has upon sickness allowance.</p>
<h2>Update 493G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - (1)Definition of work - unemployed claimants. (2)Basic Qualifications. (3)Alcohol and drug rehabilitation programs. (4)Claimants under 16 years. See guidelines 14.2400 to 14.3300.</p>
<p>(1) This amendment clarifies the definition of work for unemployed claimants as full-time, part-time permanent or casual work for at least eight hours per week that the person could be reasonably expected to do.</p>
<p>(2) This amendment corrects cross reference details and the name of the Australian Government Health Service Medical Officer and adds youth training allowance to all job search references.</p>
<p>(3) This amendment removes an incorrect cross reference.</p>
<p>(4) This amendment corrects cross reference details.</p>
<h2>Update 492G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Requalification after cancellation at week 52 or 104. See guidelines 14.4100 to 14.4153.</p>
<p>This change clarifies the existing circumstances in which sickness allowance can be regranted in the two year preclusion period and advises that a person who is awaiting surgery may now also qualify.</p>
<h2>Update 491G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - (1) Introduction and overview. See guidelines 14.300 to 14.402. (2) Not qualified for two years after cancellation due to time limits. See guidelines 14.600 to 14601.</p>
<p>(1) This amendment corrects cross reference details.</p>
<p>(2) A person who is awaiting surgery may qualify for sickness allowance during a two year preclusion period.</p>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Not qualified for two years after cancellation due to time limits. See guidelines 14.600 to 14.601.</p>
<p>A person who is awaiting surgery may qualify for sickness allowance during a two year preclusion period.</p>
<h2>Update 490G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Reviews and notification. See guideline 14.12301.</p>
<p>This amendment corrects a cross reference.</p>
<h2>Update 489G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Current Rates of Payment. See guidelines 27.5000 and 27.6700.</p>
<p>Update of rates and associated information.</p>
<h2>Update 488G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Assessable assets. See guideline 27.15556.</p>
<p>Provides the 'rule-of-thumb' calculation used to determine whether the surrender value of an insurance policy should be obtained from the insurer.</p>
<h2>Update 487G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
