<h2>Update 486G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Incorrect Act references. See guidelines 12.9000 and 12.9200.</p>
<p>Act references have been updated to reflect a renumbering of the Act.</p>
<h2>Update 485G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Non-attendance at review interview. See guideline 12.2104.</p>
<p>Non-attendance at an IRM review interview has previously been considered an activity test breach. Changes to the legislation now mean that this should be treated as an administrative breach.</p>
<h2>Update 484G # Date 19 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Jury duty. See guideline 12.171.</p>
<p>Persons performing jury duty can now be exempted from the application of the activity test under the 'special circumstances' provisions within section 525AA of the Act.</p>
<h2 id="5october1995">Update 483G # Date 5 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Portability - Return to Australia See guideline 42.900.</p>
<p>When a pensioner returns to Australia after an absence overseas, the extent of review action to be carried out depends on the length of the absence and the pensioner's financial and family situation.</p>
<h2>Update 482G # Date 5 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 47 - DROUGHT RELIEF PAYMENTS - Earnings credit eligibility for drought relief payment (DRP). See guideline 47.7000.</p>
<p>Drought relief payment recipients are not eligible for an earnings credit.</p>
<h2>Update 481G # Date 5 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 13 - FARM HOUSEHOLD SUPPORT - Earnings credit eligibility for farm household support (FHS). See guideline 13.7000.</p>
<p>Farm household support recipients are not eligible for an earnings credit.</p>
<h2>Update 480G # Date 5 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Parental Income Test/Parental Assets Test. See guideline 45.21400.</p>
<p>Form JY to be issues in cases where parents reside overseas.</p>
<h2>Update 479G # Date 5 October 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 7 - WIFE PENSION - Rates of pension. See guideline 7.2000.</p>
<p>Describes rate payable to spouse of imprisoned pensioner.</p>
<h2 id="21september1995">Update 478G # Date 21 September 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Education leavers. See guideline 45.7900.</p>
<p>Reference to the Student and Youth Assistance Act 1973 corrected.</p>
<h2>Update 477G # Date 21 September 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Residence and New Zealand citizens moving to Australia. See guidelines 45.1200 to 45.1220.</p>
<p>New sub heading of Residence and New Zealand citizens moving to Australia as youth training allowance (YTA) is not covered by the New Zealand Reciprocal Agreement therefore New Zealand citizens are not subject to a settlement test and can qualify for YTA from date of arrival in Australia.</p>
<h2>Update 476G # Date 21 September 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 2 - METHODS OF PAYMENT AND TAXATION - Weekly payment option. See guideline 2.2141.</p>
<p>Reworded to clarify effect on weekly payments when subject to 'Application for Payment' (Form SU19) lodgement.</p>
<h2>Update 475G # Date 21 September 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 8 - CARER PENSION - Definition of severely handicapped person. See guideline 8.500.</p>
<p>Clarifies that "frequent care" or "constant supervision" are alternative tests. A combination of the two should not be used as the basis to justify payment of carer pension.</p>
<h2>Update 474G # Date 21 September 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - Out of Region Lodgements - Youth Service Units. See guidelines 45.16100 to 45.16103.</p>
<p>Allows a young customer who is assigned a Youth Service Unit region code to attend their closest regional office for simple queries such as lodging their SU19.</p>
<h2>Update 473G # Date 21 September 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Out of Region Lodgements - Youth Service Units. See guidelines 12.16100 to 12.16104.</p>
<p>Allows a young customer who is assigned a Youth Service Unit region code to attend their closest regional office for simple queries such as lodging their SU19.</p>
<h2>Update 472G # Date 21 September 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 45 - YOUTH TRAINING ALLOWANCE - New Zealand Citizens moving to Australia. See guidelines 45.1210.</p>
