<h2>Update 434G # Date 10 August 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Sale of home and purchase of another. See guidelines 27.18830 to 27.18837.</p>
<p>To provide a clearer picture of how proceeds from the sale of a home should be treated under the income and asset test.</p>
<h2>Update 433G # Date 10 August 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Asset valuation of business goodwill. See guidelines 27.15813 to 27.15814.</p>
<p>Where a client can clearly demonstrate that the value of purchased business goodwill is lower than the value shown in the business records because the business is non-viable and is being wound up, or is running at a loss and cannot be sold as a going concern, the purchased goodwill can be ignored.</p>
