<h2>Update 381G # Date 18 May 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Comparable foreign payments - legislation - reasonable action. See guidelines 42.2050 to 42.2051.</p>
<p>Under the comparable foreign payment provisions, reasonable action to obtain an overseas pensioner at the highest rate possible does not involve having to seek increases in overseas pensions which become available if pensioners are in the paying country if they are visiting the paying country for less than 12 months.</p>
