<h2 id="27april1995">Update 377G # Date 27 April 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Stand down or suspension from work - person may be unemployed. See guidelines 12.115 to 12.117.</p>
<p>A person may be considered as unemployed if they are stood down or suspended from work under certain conditions.</p>
<h2>Update 376G # Date 27 April 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Deferment periods waiting period. See guidelines 12.8400 to 12.8403.</p>
<p>Deferment periods can no longer be served concurrently with waiting periods. As such, any deferment period which imposed due to a breach which occurs during a newly arrived migrant waiting period must be served after the waiting period has expired.</p>
<h2>Update 375G # Date 27 April 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Waiting and Deferment Periods 'Reduction of education leavers waiting period due to previous casual or part time employment. See guidelines 12.7710 to 12.7712.</p>
<p>The sections of the Act referred to in guideline 12.7710 currently state that an education waiting period cannot last more than six months. It should be referring to reduction of waiting periods for part time work and how to calculate the reduction (see subsections 541(5A) to 541(5C)).</p>
<h2>Update 374G # Date 27 April 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Asset valuation of governing directors shares held in a private company. See guidelines 27.15600 to 27.15609.</p>
<p>How to assess the asset value of particular shares in a private company that confers greater voting powers to the shareholder than other issued share types.</p>
