<h2>Update 361G and 362G # Date 6 April 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 27 - DETERMINING RATES OF PAYMENT - Assessing company issued or exchange traded options. See guidelines 27.15575 to 27.15576 and 27.12085 to 27.12175.</p>
<p>Company issued options should only have their asset value assessed. The asset value is based on the last sale price at the time of assessment. Details of the last sale price are available from the <cite>Financial Review</cite> or the <cite>Stock Exchange Journal</cite>. Exchange traded options are generally not income or asset tested. However, if a client requests a review, contact your State Investment Income and Assets Policy Section (II&amp;APS). If a person is an options trader, you should refer the details to your State II&amp;APS.</p>
