<h2>Update 342G # Date 9 March 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 37 - COMPENSATION RECOVERY - Inclusion of widow allowance as a 'compensation affected payment'. See guideline 37.000.</p>
<p>Widow allowance has been included as a 'compensation affected payment' under part 3.14 of the Act.</p>
<h2>Update 341G # Date 9 March 1995</h2>
<p>CHAPTER 12 - NEWSTART - Liquid assets test waiting period. See guidelines 12.7500 to 12.7503 and 12.7520.</p>
<p>1) These amendments set out the basis for applying the liquid assets test waiting period and when the waiting period is waived for transferees and those who have commenced an approved activity.</p>
<p>2) Persons are not subject to the liquid assets test waiting period if their liquid assets are below either $5000 for singles or $10000 for couples and single period with children. Under the waiting period waiver provisions there are allowable deductions in the person's liquid assets which may reduce their total liquid assets below the $5000 or $10000 maximum reserves.</p>
<h2>Update 340G # Date 9 March 1995</h2>
